get_p_kde = function(x) {
	aux = cbind(KDE$x,KDE$y)
	aux=aux[which(aux[,1]<x),]
	return(tail(aux, n=1)[2])
}

best_kde_id = 0
best_hist_id = 0
best_metric = 1000000
print(c('hist_id', 'kde_id', 'metric'))
for (hist_id in 1:length(hists)) {
	for (kde_id in 1:length(kdes)) {
		H = hists[[hist_id]]
		KDE = kdes[[kde_id]]
		centers = H$mids
		M = length(centers)
		p_H = H$density
		p_KDE = sapply(centers, get_p_kde)
		metric = sum((p_H - p_KDE)^2) / M
		print(c(hist_id, kde_id, metric))
		if (metric < best_metric) {
			best_metric = metric
			best_kde_id = kde_id
			best_hist_id = hist_id
		}
	}
}

Задача T1. Пункт 1¶

Пусть $\hat b = \max(X_1, \dots X_n), \ \hat a = \min(X_1, \dots X_n)$. Найдем $\mathbb{E} [\hat b], \mathbb{E} [\hat a]$. $$ P(\max(X_1, \dots X_n < x)) = P(X_1 < x, \dots X_n < x) = P(X_1 < x)^n = \Big( {x - a \over b - a} \Big)^n \mathbb{I}[x \in [b, a]] $$ $$ p_\max(x) = {n (x-a)^{n-1} \over (b - a)^{n}} \mathbb{I} [\dots] $$ $$ \mathbb{E} [\hat b] = \int_\mathbb{R} x p_\max (x) dx = \int_a^b {n (x-a)^{n-1} \over (b - a)^{n}} dx = {a + bn \over n + 1} $$ Далее воспольуемся тем, что $\mathbb{E} [\hat a] = b + a - \mathbb{E} [\hat b]$. Пользуясь этим получаем, что $$ \text{Bias} (\hat I_n) = \mathbb{E} [\hat b - \hat a - (b - a)] = 2 (\mathbb{E} [\hat b] - b) = 2 {a - b \over n + 1} $$

bandwidths = seq(from=0.1,to=5,by=0.1)
u = seq(from=0, to=2, by=0.01)
best_mise = 10000
for (k in 1:length(bandwidths)) {
	kde = density(X, kernel='epanechnikov', bw=bandwidths[k])
	p_pred = sapply(u, get_p_kde)
	p_true = sapply(u, get_p_true)
	mise = sum((p_pred - p_true)^2) / length(u)
	if (mise < best_mise) {
		best_mise = mise
	}
	print(c(bandwidths[k], mise))
}

In [60]:
inside = function(x) {
	abs(x) <= 1
}
phi0 = function(x) {
	1 / sqrt(2)
}
phi1 = function(x) {
	sqrt(3 / 2) * x
}
phi2 = function(x) {
	sqrt(5 / 8) * (3 * x^2 - 1)
}
legandre_kernel = function(y, x, h) {
	t = abs(y - x)
	(phi0(0) * phi0(t) + phi1(0) * phi1(t) + phi2(0) * phi2(t)) * inside(t) 
}
k1 <- list(
	kernel = legandre_kernel,
	support = c(-Inf, Inf)
)
out = kdensity(X, kernel = k1, bw = 0.1)
plot(out)
